item.title: Jenn add a quote by Emily Dickinson
item.description: "Existence has overpowered Books. Today I slew a Mushroom." -- Emily Dickinson

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Stephen King
item.description: "Any word you have to hunt for in a thesaurus is the wrong word. There are no exceptions to this rule." -- Stephen King

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Burt Bacharach
item.description: "A synonym is a word you use when you can't spell the word you first thought of." -- Burt Bacharach

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Mark Twain
item.description: "The difference between the right word and the almost right word is the difference between lightning and a lightning bug." -- Mark Twain

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Oliver Wendell Holmes Sr.
item.description: "The morning cup of coffee has an exhilaration about it which the cheering influence of the afternoon or evening cup of tea cannot be expected to reproduce." -- Oliver Wendell Holmes Sr.

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Nicholas Negroponte
item.description: "Computing is not about computers anymore. It is about living." -- Nicholas Negroponte

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Erich Fromm
item.description: "Creativity requires the courage to let go of certainties." -- Erich Fromm

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Gwendolyn Brooks
item.description: "Poetry is life distilled." -- Gwendolyn Brooks

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Dave Barry
item.description: "You can only be young once. But you can always be immature." -- Dave Barry

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Thomas A. Edison
item.description: "I have not failed. I've just found 10,000 ways that won't work." -- Thomas A. Edison

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Warren Buffett
item.description: "You can't produce a baby in one month by getting nine women pregnant." -- Warren Buffett

item.title: Jenn add a quote by John le Carré
item.description: "A desk is a dangerous place from which to view the world." -- John le Carré

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Jeph Jacques
item.description: "There are two ways to pass a hurdle: leaping over or plowing through... There needs to be a monster truck option." -- Jeph Jacques

item.title: Jenn add a quote by André Gide
item.description: "One does not discover new lands without consenting to lose sight of the shore for a very long time." -- André Gide

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Oscar Wilde
item.description: "Always forgive your enemies; nothing annoys them so much." -- Oscar Wilde

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Marilyn Monroe
item.description: "I believe that everything happens for a reason. People change so that you can learn to let go, things go wrong so that you appreciate them when they're right, you believe lies so you eventually learn to trust no one but yourself, and sometimes good things fall apart so better things can fall together." -- Marilyn Monroe

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Nathaniel Hawthorne
item.description: "Be true! Be true! Be true! Show freely to the world, if not your worst, yet some trait whereby the worst may be inferred!" -- Nathaniel Hawthorne

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Brooks Atkinson
item.description: "The virtue of the camera is not the power it has to transform the photographer into an artist, but the impulse it gives him to keep on looking." -- Brooks Atkinson

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Victoria Holt
item.description: "Never regret. If it's good, it's wonderful. If it's bad, it's experience." -- Victoria Holt

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Benjamin Franklin
item.description: "Never confuse Motion with Action." -- Benjamin Franklin

item.title: Jenn add a quote by John Maxwell
item.description: "Leadership is not about titles, positions or flowcharts. It is about one life influencing another." -- John Maxwell

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Robert Harris
item.description: "What is leadership, after all, but the blind choice of one route over another and the confident pretense that the decision was based on reason" -- Robert Harris

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Patrick Lencioni
item.description: "Remember teamwork begins by building trust. And the only way to do that is to overcome our need for invulnerability." -- Patrick Lencioni

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Ralph Nadar
item.description: "I start with the premise that the function of leadership is to produce more leaders not more followers." -- Ralph Nadar

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Lao Tzu
item.description: "A leader is best When people barely know he exists Of a good leader, who talks little, When his work is done, his aim fulfilled, They will say, “We did this ourselves." -- Lao Tzu

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Pierre Teilhard de Chardin
item.description: "Our duty, as men and women, is to proceed as if limits to our ability did not exist. We are collaborators in creation." -- Pierre Teilhard de Chardin

item.title: Jenn add a quote by John Maxwell
item.description: "To collaborative team members, completing one another is more important than competing with one another." -- John Maxwell

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Clay Shirky
item.description: "[C]ollaborative production is simple: no one person can take credit for what gets created, and the project could not come into being without the participation of many." -- Clay Shirky

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Matthew Woodring Stover
item.description: "If you take out the team in teamwork, it's just work. Now who wants that?" -- Matthew Woodring Stover

item.title: Jenn add a quote by Patrick Lencioni
item.description: "It's as simple as this. When people don't unload their opinions and feel like they've been listened to, they won't really get on board." -- Patrick Lencioni
